<HEADLINE> Iraqi-Russian Oil Contract to be Implemented </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The contract signed by Iraq and
Russia on developing the West Al-Qaranah oilfield, the second
phase, will be implemented soon after being approved by the
governments of both countries, the Iraqi television reported today.
</P>
<P>
The television quoted Salman Negm, acting chief of the oil and
power committee of the Iraqi National Assembly, as saying that
during the term of the 23-year contract, the total production of
the oilfield is expected to reach 4.4 billion barrels.
</P>
<P>
The West Al-Qaranah is one of the 10 oilfields that were marked
by Iraq for development during the last few years in cooperation
with major international companies from Russia, France and China.
</P>
<P>
The contract signed here in March on the heels of the second
session of the Iraqi-Russian Joint Committee for Economic, Trade
and Technical Cooperation, is expected to be implemented after the
U.N.-imposed sanctions on Iraq is lifted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
