<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Meets Iranian Parliament Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
met Iranian parliament speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri in the
Kremlin today, Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Yeltsin said he was satisfied with
Russian-Iranian relations and cooperation. A sound beneficial
cooperation had been established between Russia and Iran and this
was further developing.
</P>
<P>
The range of cooperation between Russia and Iran, in Yeltsin's
opinion, was reason enough to say that relations between the two
states would develop and strengthen further.
</P>
<P>
Nateq-Nouri also expressed his satisfaction with the
Iranian-Russian relations.
</P>
<P>
At a plenary session of the Russian State Duma (the lower house)
after the meeting, Nateq-Nouri said Iranian-Russian relations were
based "on a stable foundation, long-term prospects and unchanging
interests."
</P>
<P>
He hoped to increase economic cooperation with Russia,
including cooperation in energy sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
