<HEADLINE> Macedonia: Bonn Backs Its Seeking of EU, NATO Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Germany will support the efforts
made by the Republic of Macedonia to join the European Union (EU)
and the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), Macedonian
Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference at the end of his three-day visit
to Germany, Crvenkovski also admitted that his country still had
to make great efforts before it could achieve full membership in
either body.
</P>
<P>
At their meeting earlier today, Crvenkovski and German Foreign
Minister Klaus Kinkel signed an agreement under which Germany
pledged 30 million marks (about 17.5 million U.S. dollars) in aid
for a railway project linking Macedonia and Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
The Macedonian prime minister also met German Chancellor Helmut
Kohl and Finance Minister Theo Waigel during the past two days.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed with Waigel, Germany will take over
174 million marks (101 million dollars) of Macedonia's foreign
debt to arrange payment rescheduling over the next 15 years.
</P>
