<DOCNO> XIE19970412.0032 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 275,000 Ethiopeans in Afar Need Emergency Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia today said more
than 275,000 people in the northern Afar regional state are in
need of emergency food aid due to lack of rainfall in the past
year.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ethiopian News Agency, a team
of experts from the Central Disaster Prevention and Preparedness
Commission has toured the drought areas and confirmed the
calamities.
</P>
<P>
The pasturalists were in short of milk supply due to the dry
grazing land and lack of water in the drought affected areas, and
flocks of goats perished due to failure in taking urgent measures
to stamp out animal diseases resulted from recurrent drought,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
This is the second drought affected areas announced by the
Ethiopian government since last month. The nation said last month
that nearly one million people needed emergency food aid in three
southern states, namely the Somali, Oromiya, and the Southern
People's states.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia attained the second consecutive bumper agricultural
harvest in 1996/97 with grain output of 11. 7 million tons, a
20.6 percent increase over the previous 9.7 million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
