<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-11 18:27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Develops Advanced Computer-Controlled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Israeli researchers have
developed a labor and cost-saving harvester, a robotic device
programmed by farmers to pick exactly the amount and type of
produce required with no human intervention.
</P>
<P>
The harvester developed by researchers of the Israeli Greentech
Company is designed for stationary growing environments, such as
tomatoes, cucumbers, melons, eggplants and peppers in greenhouse,
according to a report of Israel Export Institute. It can work
vertically and horizontally.
</P>
<P>
The device, 2 meters high, can reach up to 2.5 meters. It is
composed of a computer, a controller, image processing tools
and arm.
</P>
<P>
The "pick head" can be changed according to the shape of fruit
being collected. Using the control panel, farmers input the
color, size and weight of the produce to be picked and the robot
harvester starts picking, identifying the correct fruit using its
image processing capabilities.
</P>
<P>
The harvester reportedly can pick 80 kilograms of tomatoes
weighing 170-200 grams per hour. The robot can work 24
hours a day and its performance can be observed by installing a
video camera in the greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
The invention not only frees farm hands from extremely hard
work in the greenhouse due to the humid atmosphere and high
temperature and pressures, but also halve labor requirements.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
