<HEADLINE> Cholera Claims 48 Lives In Tanzania Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Cholera disease which
started in January has so far claimed 48 lives and affected 957
people in different parts of of the capital here.
</P>
<P>
Health Commissioner of Dar es Salaam City Commission (DCC)
Matiku Nyakarungu made this disclosure here today, saying that
the killer disease which started at five different areas, has now
covered more areas.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic is spreading at a high speed because of the
on-going rains and people's negligence to health rules, according
to the health commissioner.
</P>
<P>
Nyakarungu said the city commission is finalizing plans to
establish new cholera emergency centers at Mbagala and Manzese in
addition to the eight existing ones, so that victims are treated
in time and their movement restricted to control the epidemic
spread.
</P>
<P>
He further said the Tanzanian government and different
international organizations are working hand-in-hand with the
city commission in curbing the killer disease by funding.
</P>
<P>
Cholera dehydrates the human body extremely fast through
purging and vomiting and can kill the victim within three hours
of the first symptoms if proper treatment is not administered.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
