<HEADLINE> Prawns Ships Licensed In Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Eight ships have been
granted fishing licenses for catching prawns this season, Daily
News reported today.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Chairman of Tanzania Seamen Union (TASU) Maulid H. Maulid
was quoted as saying that two more fishing vessels will be
licensed later and they will employ about 50 seamen.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports, the fishing season this year has
been curtailed from nine months to eight by the Department of
Fisheries to allow proper breeding of prawns in the Indian Ocean.
</P>
<P>
Normally, the nine-month prawn fishing season start in March
and ends in November, but now will begin from March to October.
</P>
</TEXT>
