<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-11 18:55 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lychee Treatment System Developed In Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Based on research by the
Israeli Volcani Institute, IMA Engineering Ltd. has developed a
Lychee Treatment System (LTS) that ensures shelf-life of at
least four weeks, enabling successful marketing of the fruit to
the desired markets.
</P>
<P>
The LTS offers natural post-harvest treatment, sorting and
packing for shipment, according to a report of Israel Export
Institute.
</P>
<P>
Capable of handling 1000 kilograms per hour, it consists of
five stations: an elevator for moving the fruit from picking
boxes to the dipping unit; the "heart" of the system, where post
harvest treatment is carried out; a dryer; sorting unit and
packing unit.
</P>
<P>
The equipment is easy to install and to transport. During
1994-96 seasons, the system was tested successfully on a
commercial level both in Israel and Thailand, with excellent
European market response.
</P>
<P>
Treated fruits were also exported to the U.S..
</P>
<P>
Because of its very short shelf life (about four days), most
of the 600,000 tons of lychee produced in the world is sold at a
very low price for canning. But demand for fresh quality lychee
is growing and the U.S., European and Japanese markets offer high
prices and profits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
