<HEADLINE> Gowda Government Voted out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The 10-month-old United Front
(UF) government headed by Deve Gowda was voted out in the lower
house of parliament late tonight with no alternative in sight so
far except the hope for a fresh tie up with the Congress Party
under a new leader.
</P>
<P>
A one-line motion moved by Gowda was defeated with 158 for, 292
against and 6 in absence.
</P>
<P>
Following the defeat of the government after an 11 hour-long
debate in Parliament here in the special sitting, the UF Steering
Committee will be meeting early tomorrow morning amidst
speculations that it might elect a new leader to revive the
relationship with the Congress, which withdrew its support to the
UF government on March 30.
</P>
<P>
The Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP), the biggest opposition party
in the country, has said that it would not stake claim to form the
next government unless it was sure of commanding majority support
in parliament.
</P>
<P>
The vote on the motion, which said "the house expresses
confidence in the council of ministers," came after a whole day of
hectic debates on it in the Lok Sabha (the lower house of
parliament).
</P>
<P>
The motion was moved by the prime minister at the request of
President Shanker Dayal Sharma following the Congress party
withdrew support to the government 13 days ago.  
</P>
</TEXT>
