<HEADLINE> Zairian New PM Forms Cabinet Dominated by Generals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KINSHASA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Zaire's new prime minister,
General Likulia Bolongo, today nominated a new cabinet which
includes two army generals to serve as defense and interior
ministers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Bolongo maintained the foreign minister, Gerard
Kamanda wa Kamanda, in his cabinet, which is the first Zairian
government to be headed by an army general since the democratic
transition began in the country in 1990.
</P>
<P>
General Mahele Liyoko, the chief of staff of the Zairian army,
was nominated as defense minister, and General Ilunga, the chief
of staff of President Mobutu Sese Seko, was nominated interior
minister.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet has altogether 28 members, including two woman
ministers.
</P>
<P>
General Bolongo said that he would "pacify" the country,
continue to negotiate with the rebels, "clean up" the public
finance and restructure the army in order to set up a "republican
army for protecting human rights and liberty."
</P>
<P>
Bolongo was nominated by President Mobutu Wednesday to replace
Etienne Tshisekedi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
