<HEADLINE> Heavy Rain Eases Prolonged Drought in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Somalia is now receiving
considerable rain after almost two years of prolonged droughts
which hit many regions in the country.
</P>
<P>
As the droughts, diseases and the related malnourishment have
claimed the lives of many people and livestock, now the long
expected rain has brought hope to people while creating
difficulties in parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Many key streets linking the southern port city of Kismayu to
its nearby towns of Jamame, Badhadhe, Afmadow and Dhobley have
been cut off by the rains which have fallen in Lower Jubba Region
during the last few days.
</P>
<P>
The tarmac road especially linking Kismayu with Mogadishu has
also been affected by rain water.
</P>
<P>
The hazards created by the rain have mainly jeopardized the
commercial activities from Mogadishu to Kismayu and to the
central regions.
</P>
<P>
However, the herdsmen and nomads are happy about the new life
their herds are looking forward to.
</P>
<P>
As usual, in seven days time, the pastoral land will be filled
with new grass for the cattle and sheep to graze while the goats
and camels which rely on trees will also enjoy the new leaves in
10 days time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
