<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Parliament Elects Deputy Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's House of
Federation has elected Mohammed Seraheyon as deputy speaker.
</P>
<P>
According to an announcement by the office of the House of
Federation today, Mohammed who was the only candidate
representing the Somali Regional State was unanimously elected at
a session of federation.
</P>
<P>
Ziad Bederi who served as deputy speaker of parliament for one
year was removed both from his post and membership, the office
added.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian parliament is composed of two houses, the House
of People's Representatives and the House of Federation.
</P>
<P>
Members of the House of People's Representatives are elected
from candidates in each electoral district by a plurality of the
votes cast.
</P>
<P>
Members of House of Federation are representatives from
nationalities. The House of Federation has the power to interpret
the constitution and strive to find solution to disputes or
misunderstandings that may arise between states. 
</P>
