<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Italy's 11-months-old government won
a vote of confidence in parliament's lower house Saturday,
clearing a challenge from the right-wing opposition seeking to
block a security force for stricken Albania.
</P>
<P>
The center-left government led by Prime Minister Romano Prodi
won by 321 votes to 166, with one abstention. The vote was taken
after the Refoundation Communist Party, which earlier broke ranks
with the government, returned to support Prodi's party.
</P>
