all respect them for their great role."
</P>
<P>
A 15-year old student Wednesday shot twice and seriously
injured his science teacher Mutaz Mahmoud Ibrahim, 35, in
Asmaei Secondary School campus for failing him in geology. The
teacher who was injured in his stomach, lung and liver is
still in critical condition and remaining in a hospital's
intensive care unit.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait has nearly 800 foreign teachers in various schools
who are from various Arab and English speaking countries.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti scholars and officials polled by a local daily
today expressed their grave concern and called on tough
punishment of the misbehaviors of the youths in the small
traditional Islamic Gulf state.
</P>
<P>
They said recurring incidents of violence at the country's
schools are grounds enough for the government and National
Assembly to tackle the situation on a firm footing.
</P>
<P>
Al-Haroun hoped such incidents would not take place any
more under any circumstances and said the ministry would not
allow such incidents to occur again.
</P>
<P>
He also said Kuwaiti government had taken all legal
measures to punish the attacker. 
</P>
