<HEADLINE> Results of Chinese Ethnic Minorities' Vocal Music Contest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The results of China's first
ethnic minorities' vocal music contest were announced in Nanning,
the capital of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, Friday night.
</P>
<P>
The first prizes, of the 40 awards, went to Yang Shuguang
(female, from Tu ethnic group, from the Conservatory of Chinese
Music), Qu Xuexuan (male, from Man ethnic group, from the
Conservatory of Chinese Music), Danzim (male, Tibetan, from
Tibet), Huang Chunyan (female, from Zhuang ethnic group, from
Guangxi).
</P>
<P>
There were 9 second prizes, 16 third prizes, 10 excellents, and
one extra.
</P>
<P>
The panel of judges consisted of prominent Chinese vocal music
experts, who included Jin Tielin, Li Shuangjiang and Zhang Yuenan.
</P>
<P>
The contest was sponsored by the Ministry of Culture, the State
Nationalities Affairs Commission, the Ministry of Radio, Film and
Television, and the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region. 
</P>
