<HEADLINE> Lofty Goals For China Science and Technology University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A project to build China Science
and Technology University into one of the most important teaching
and research centers in China was recently kicked off officially
with approval from the State Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
The project is part of "Project 211" which will select the 100
best universities in China to be given preferential treatment and
special support in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The central government will spend 200 million yuan (nearly 25
million US dollars) on the university during the Ninth Five-Year
Plan period (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
China Science and Technology University was founded in 1958 in
Beijing and then moved to Hefei, the capital of east China's Anhui
province, in 1970. It was part of the first group selected for
"Project 211."
</P>
<P>
It is one of the key universities in China, and one of the top
four in terms of the number of papers published in international
journals. 
</P>
