<HEADLINE> Visa International Looking for Bigger Role in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Edmund Jensen, President of the
credit card group, Visa International, has pledged greater
cooperation with Chinese banks to promote its business in China,
and to provide the world's most advanced technology here.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 20 million Visa cards in China at present,
but the figure is expected to rise to 200 million by 2003, or
about a fifth of the world's total.
</P>
<P>
Ten Chinese banks have become the member banks of Visa
International, with six of them hooked up to the global network.
</P>
<P>
With its sophisticated electronic payment system, Visa
International has played an important role in China's credit card
promotion by co-operating closely with the credit card training
center of the central bank.
</P>
<P>
Visa International now has representative office in Beijing and
Shanghai.  
</P>
</TEXT>
