<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Afrobeat king Fela
Anikulapo-Kuti was arrested for Indian hemp consumption on
Wednesday by the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA),
local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Answering questions of Major-General Musa Bamaiyi, the
chairman of NDLEA, at a news conforence in Lagos on Friday, Fela
reportedly said that hemp is not drug but a medicinal grass,
which he has been taking for 40 years and is good to his health
and composition.
</P>
<P>
He said he knows that hard drugs like cocaine and heroine are
bad and don't take them, nor does he encourage people to take
them.
</P>
<P>
The NDLEA recovered 10 kilograms of Indian hemp from Fela's
house in a raid last year, but raised no charges against him.
Instead, it tried to rehabilitate him.
</P>
<P>
But over the past one year, Major-General Bamaiyi said, Fela
"has remained unrepentant in his bad habit. His followership
seems to be on the increase daily."
</P>
<P>
Fela's activities "have held many innocent souls hostage and
with the gloom now pervading their lives, they are doomed if the
agency fails in its sacred responsibility of rescuing their
enslaved souls from his clutches", he said.
</P>
<P>
"Drastic disease needs drastic surgery to get proper cure," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Arrested together with Fela are 106 others in his shrine and
house, including many teenagers, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Fela himself contriubted the failed rehabilitation to a
"communication gap" between him and the NDLEA. 
</P>
