<HEADLINE> Fighting Breaks Peace in Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The noise of heavy machine
guns and rocket propelled grenades have today awakened the Somali
people in the war torn capital, Mogadishu, after having been
enjoying relative peace for about two months now.
</P>
<P>
Mogadishu citizens hopeful of lasting peaceful settlemtnt to
the political crises have been frightened by the unexpected
fighting in the heart of the capital.
</P>
<P>
At least seven people were killed and more than 17 others were
wounded when armed confrontation erupted between rival militiamen
loyal to north Mogadishu faction leader, Mr Ali Mahdi Mohamed, in
Bermuda neighborhood of central Mogadishu today. The clashes
which began with high intensity have cooled down to sporadic
shootings in the area in south Mogadishu. Ten of the seriosly
wounded people were rushed to north Mogadishu's ICRC run Keysaney
hospital, while few others were taken to medical treatments in
south Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the fighting is not yet officially disclosed,
however sources close to the area said the fighting began
following the nomination of a new district commissioner for the
area by Ali Mahdi Mohamed. According to the report, the
nomination of the new man backed by the people in Waberi district
was immediately opposed by militia commanders in Sigale area who
reportedly have killed the former commissioner, late Ibrahim
Shurie late last month.
</P>
<P>
The opposition group have reportedly attacked the residence of
the new commissioner killing two of his men in the house and
dislodged his supporters. The fighting has intensified as the
attack and counter-attack efforts by the militiamen of the
warring sides continued in the early hours of the day. However,
the area has become relatively calm before mid day.
</P>
<P>
A number of militiamen in the area said the new commissioner,
Mr Abdullahi Berhod, and the committee that supports him are not
trust worthy. They accused the local authority for misusing the
funds and the logistical supports from Mr Ali Mahdi of north
Mogadishu. The opposition group has also claimed that elements
against Ali Mahdi himself are behind the destabilization of
Bermuda.
</P>
<P>
There has been several attempts in solving the crises between
the two group who both support Mr Ali Mahdi Mohamed. Bermuda
neighborhood which situates in the heart of the capital, 200-400
meters north of Mogadishu's sea and airports, consists of four
portions from four different districts: Hawlwadag, Hodon, Waberi
and Hamar Ja-Jab.
</P>
<P>
Each of the three main clans of Mogadishu, Abgal, Habar Gidir
and Murusadeh, occupies parts of these four districts. The areas
controlled by the Habar Gidir and Murusadeh clans have remained
unaffected by the fighting today. The area has got its name,
Bermuda, during the height of the war between late general
Mohamed Farah Aidid and Ali Mahdi Mohamed in 1991-1992 following
Aidid's failure to capture the neighborhood. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
