<HEADLINE> Hong Kong SAR Preparatory Committee Panel Meets in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A panel working on means of
selecting the first Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) held its second meeting in Beijing,
from April 11 to 12.
</P>
<P>
Panel members say that people from various parts of Hong Kong
society made many suggestions on the method of selecting the first
Legislative Council during the panel's period of consultation in
Hong Kong last month.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed a report on the consultation complied by
the Secretariat of the Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong SAR,
and said the report is a fairly objective review of the opinions
of Hong Kong people overall.
</P>
<P>
The panel held a discussion of these opinions on the selection
method and is set to suggest an outline at its next meeting. From
March 1 to 31, the panel held consultations on the selection
method.
</P>
<P>
By the end of the consultation period, it had received 972
suggestion papers from 305 organizations and 655 people, mainly
focused on a direct election system by geographical location, the
establishment of nine new functional bodies, and the composition
of the election committee.
</P>
<P>
These papers include opinions on how to limit the number of
Legislative Council members who are not Chinese or who have the
right of abode in foreign countries to not more than 20 percent of
the total number of members. 
</P>
