<HEADLINE> Bonded Zone in Tianjin Reports Record Economic Quotas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Port Bonded Zone set
records in all economic quotas in the first quarter of this year,
retaining its leading position among bonded zones in China.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show the zone turned out a GDP of 366 million
yuan in the first quarter, representing a growth of 113 percent
over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The value of cargo flow through the zone reached 610 million US
dollars, up 46 percent. It reported a trade volume of 207 million
US dollars, and a committed overseas investment of 125 million US
dollars, rising 130 percent and 23 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Established in May 1991 and opening the following April, the
Tianjin Port Bonded Zone has become the largest bonded zone in
northern China.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1.2 billion yuan has been invested in infrastructure
in the seven sq km bonded area.
</P>
<P>
Investors from 73 countries and regions, and 25 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions in China, have set up more
than 3,000 businesses in the zone, with a total committed
investment of over three billion US dollars including two billion
in overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
To date, the accumulated value of cargo flow through the zone
has exceeded six billion US dollars, and more than 6,000 TEU of
international cargo containers went into and out of the zone each
month.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the zone handled 460 million US dollars-worth of
exports, and goods for entrepot trade valued at more than 130
million US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
