things clear that he was not a contender for any office and that
the UF should elect a new leader to replace Deve Gowda so as to
win continued support of the Congress in forming a new government.
</P>
<P>
He indicated that the talks with the UF would be resumed once
it changed its leader.
</P>
<P>
When asked whether the Congress would join a new UF government
or support it from outside, he said that it was for the party
chief to decide.
</P>
<P>
