<HEADLINE> APL Initiates First Highway-Ocean Intermodal Line in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 12 (Xinhua) -- American President Lines (APL),
one of the world's ten leading shipping companies, has initiated
its first highway-ocean intermodal shipping line in China.
</P>
<P>
The new line enables the shipping of cargo containers from
Nanjing to Shanghai via a newly built expressway between the two
cities, then to ports around the world via its regular ocean
shipping services starting from the Shanghai port.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the traditional shipping route on the Yangtze
River, it now takes two, four, and six days less to transport
cargo from cities in the Yangtze River Delta area such as Nanjing
to North America, the Middle East and Europe respectively.
</P>
<P>
"As a main consumer goods and industrial parts supplier in the
world, China's importance is growing," said Chen Zuoyi, APL's
general manager for China.
</P>
<P>
He added that APL will endeavor to help manufacturers and
retailers to expand their business from coastal areas to the
inland areas of China.
</P>
<P>
APL has incorporated seven Chinese coastal ports like Shanghai,
Dalian and Qingdao into its global ocean shipping network. It
started an railway-ocean intermodal shipping service from Harbin
to Dalian last November.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
