<HEADLINE> Poverty Relief for Ethnic Minority People in China's Eastern Part </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The Jingning She Autonomous
County in east China's Zhejiang Province has lifted nearly 100,000
local people out of poverty in recent years, according to a local
source.
</P>
<P>
The county, which is in a mountainous area in the central part
of the province, has tried every means possible to tap its
resources and has made considerable progress in developing small
hydro-electric power stations, forestry, and Chinese medicine.
</P>
<P>
It has spent 57 million yuan in the power sector and developed
54 small power stations with a total generating capacity of 14,300
kw.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the county has built 36 mining and smelting
enterprises, with annual output value totalling over 100 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the county produced 100 million yuan worth of
mushrooms, which won a gold prize at the Second National
Agricultural Fair.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, average per capita income in the county was 787 yuan
and the percentage of people living in poverty in the county
dropped to seven percent from 70 percent some five years ago.
</P>
