<HEADLINE> Macao Governor Confident in Macao's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira
has said that he is confident in Macao's future which was designed
by the Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration.
</P>
<P>
The governor made these remarks on the eve of the 10th
anniversary of the joint declaration, which is observed on April
13.
</P>
<P>
"Macao will continue to be a place where people can live and
work happily," he said. "Those who choose to live in Macao will
continue to be respected, and the Portuguese people residing in
Macao will continue to live harmoniously with the Chinese people."
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the joint declaration, saying it is "a
pioneering undertaking jointly created by both Portugal and
China."
</P>
<P>
The past ten years have proved that the joint efforts by both
countries are fruitful, which in turn increases confidence in the
future, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We are marching forward along a right way," the governor said.
"The policy of 'one country, two systems' means a very flexible
way in resolving questions. Macao will be a model in implementing
that policy."  
