<HEADLINE> Islamists Massacre 22 Civilians in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-two civilians were massacred
by Islamic militants Friday night in Douar Menaa near Boufarik, 35
kilometers south of the Algerian capital Algiers, the Agence
France-Presse (AFP) quoted Algerian security forces as saying
today.
</P>
<P>
Security forces accused "a group of terrorists" -- which is
apparently referring to the militant group, Armed Islamic Group --
of "cowardly" committing the massacre.
</P>
<P>
No further details were given on the circumstances of the
killing, said AFP.
</P>
<P>
At least 132 civilians were killed in the past eight days in
Algeria by Islamic militants.
</P>
<P>
Seventeen other people, most of them women and children, were
killed a few days ago in the village of Amroussa in the region of
Boufarik.
</P>
<P>
The massacres took place at the same time when Algerian
security forces were launching sweep operations, sometimes
accompanied by bombings and military helicopters, against the
Islamists' hiding places in the mountainous south and southwest
parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The operations were launched to prepare for the country's
legislative elections scheduled for June 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
