<HEADLINE> Boycott Discussions of NATO's Eastward Expansion: Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Gennady Zyuganov, chairman of the
Russian People's Patriotic Union, said today that the union is
making efforts to persuade parliament members of the European
nations to boycott discussions of NATO's eastward expansion.
</P>
<P>
"Many European parliaments, including those of France, Italy,
Greece and Spain, do not agree to NATO's enlargement plan,"
Zyuganov, who is also leader of the Russian Communist Party, was
quoted as saying in St. Petersburg by the Inter-fax news agency.
</P>
<P>
The union, established in August 1996, is the largest
opposition movement in Russia.
</P>
<P>
Zyuganov reiterated Russia's stand of strong opposition to
NATO's eastward expansion, saying that is "a major threat to
Russia."
</P>
<P>
NATO is expected to meet in Madrid this July to review the
first group of countries applying for NATO membership, namely
Poland, the Czech Republic and Hungary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
