<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Russia's industrial output in the
first quarter of 1997 grew by 0.7 percent as compared with the same
period of last year, the State Statistics Committee said today.
</P>
<P>
Different to the previous years, industrial output started to
pick up since the beginning of 1997 with February reporting a growth
rate of five percent, the committee said.
</P>
<P>
By sectors, growth in that of nonferrous metal, medicine and
microbe industries was the biggest registering six, five and two
percent respectively, while that in engineering, and chemistry and
petroleum reported only one and 0.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, output in other sectors declined. Statistics show that
output of glass and ceramic industries sector dropped by 13
percent, forest and construction materials, 11 percent, food,
power, fuel and ferrous metal, eight, six, 0.6 and 0.5 percent.
