<HEADLINE> Nepali House Speaker Calls for Action Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A parliamentary leader of Nepal
has urged to curb the rampant corruption in the society through
building up public opinion and social pressure.
</P>
<P>
Lower House Speaker Ram Chandra Poudel said here Friday that no
one has yet been able to relieve the country of the corruption
problem despite all the claims to stop it.
</P>
<P>
He told a meeting of the Public Administration Association of
Nepal (PAAN) that activities detrimental to democratic values and
norms are taking place in the country with the power of money.
</P>
<P>
Citing the often undesired implementation of development
projects on the district level, mostly attributed to the
involvement of corruption, the speaker said that the inflow of
foreign loans and assistance has contributed to the spread of
corruption in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
He called on Nepali intellectuals, the main force of the 1990
popular movement to usher in the multi-party parliamentary system,
to lead another "revolution" against corruption.  
</P>
