<HEADLINE> American MacPhie Enters Salem Open Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 11 (Xinhua) -- American qualifier Brian
MacPhie edged Canada's Sebastien Lareau 6-3, 6-3 in the
quarter-finals to enter the semi-finals of the Salem Open tennis
tournament on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old MacPhie earlier outclassed second-seed Swiss
Marc Rosset 7-6 (7-2), 6-2 in the second round.
</P>
<P>
Also advancing to the semi-finals were top-seed Michael Chang
of the United States, Sweden's Thomas Johansson and Australia's
Patrick Rafter in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Rafter downed his third-seed compatriot Todd Woodbridge 6-3,
6-1 in the quarter-finals after earlier beating German qualifer
Carsten Arriens 4-6, 7-6 (7-3), 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Chang moved into the semi-finals with a 6-1, 7-6 (7-5) victory
over seventh-seed David Prinosil of Germany. Earlier Chang
completed a 6-4, 4-6, 6-1 victory over his compatriot Jeff
Tarango in a second-round match that was suspended on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chang will meet fourth-seed Johansson, who defeated American
Justin Gimelstob 6-4, 6-4 in the quarter-finals. 
</P>
