<HEADLINE> Radulescu Edges Washington in Indian Tennis Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Fifth-seeded Alex Radulescu of
Germany beat third seed MaliVai Washington of the United States
6-3, 6-4 Friday, snatching a semi-final berth at the Gold Flake
Open tennis tournament in Madras.
</P>
<P>
Top three seeds have all tumbled out of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Richard Krajicek of the Netherlands was upset by
Andrei Pavel of Romania in straight sets on Thursday and second
seed Thomas Enqvist of Sweden withdrew from his opening match to
Germany's Rainer Schuttler on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Pavel also reached the semi-finals by beating Magnus Norman of
Sweden 6-0, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Another Swede Michael Tillstrom downed fourth-seeded American
Jonathan Stark 6-4, 6-3 and Gerard Solves of France beat Schuttler
6-4, 1-6, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
In the semi-finals Saturday, Tillstrom will play against Pavel
and Radulescu will meet Solves. 
