<HEADLINE> Brazil's Farm Goods, Livestock Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's farm goods and
livestock exports reached 805 million U.S. dollars in March, a 58
percent increase over the same month of 1996, the Brazilian
Ministry of Industry, Commerce and Tourism reported today.
</P>
<P>
Farm goods and livestock exports were 21 percent of the 3.8
billion dollar total sales abroad registered in that month by
Brazil, the ministry said in a report released to the press.
</P>
<P>
Coffee exports were worth 263 million dollars, and soybean
exports brought 310 million dollars in March. Coffee sales abroad
increased 224.69 percent and soybeans 150 percent in March of
1997, compared to the same month of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Last year, farm goods and livestock exports reached 13.2
billion dollars, 26.4 percent of the total exports of 50 billion
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
