called for greater effort to accelerate the reform and development
of the State-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A swelling inflow of foreign capital into north China's
Hebei Province, which embraces and has been in the shadows of the
two municipalities of Beijing and Tianjin, is helping build the
Bohai Bay Rim into the country's third fastest-developing region.
</P>
<P>
Overseas capital inflow to Hebei reached 2.8 billion US dollars
between 1991-1995, with that of last year alone standing at 1.6
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Visiting World Bank Vice President Jean-Michel Severino
pledged to strengthen cooperation with China, saying that annual
lending to China will remain at nearly three billion US dollars in
the next three fiscal years.
</P>
<P>
-- A new code of conduct of the Communist Party of China will
enforce more rigorous rules of Party discipline among its members.
</P>
<P>
"China Youth Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A total of 156 Chinese cities have established a social
security system guaranteeing the residents' most basic needs for a
living.
</P>
<P>
-- General Secretary of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC)
Central Committee Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng has entrusted
State Council Luo Gan to call the secretary of the CPC Committee
of the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Wang Lequan, for a report
on the effects of an earthquake that hit the northwestern region
Friday. 
