<HEADLINE> United Arab Emirates Beats Bahrain in World Cup Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Adel Mohammed scored twice to lead
the United Arab Emirates (UAE) to roll over Bahrain 2-1 in Asia's
first round Group Three World Cup qualifying tournament in Manama,
Bahrain, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain played a mostly defensive match but launched last-ditch
attacks in the final minutes and created an opportunity for Hameed
Darwish, who scored Bahrain's only goal in the last minute.
</P>
<P>
The victory gave the UAE four points from two games. Jordan,
which drew 0-0 with the UAE on Tuesday, faces Bahrain on Monday in
the final match of the group's first phase.
</P>
<P>
The group next week will move to the UAE for the final three
matches. Only the winner of the three-team group advances to the
second round. 
</P>
