<HEADLINE> Beijing-Hong Kong-London Air Route Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Air China, the largest modern
civil aviation company in China, held a ceremony here this evening
to mark the opening of the Beijing-Hong kong- London air route.
</P>
<P>
The new route, using Boeing 747 passenger plane, is scheduled
to fly once a week. A single flight will take 12 hours. Air
China opened Beijing-London direct route in 1980.
</P>
<P>
So far, the company has a total of 37 international air routes
and 107 domestic ones with a large fleet of Boeing airliners of
different type.
</P>
<P>
With a record of 42-year safety operation, Air China has been
awarded the honorary medal by the International Civil Aviation
Organization.  
</P>
