<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Muslim Official Hints Rejection of Belgrade Proposal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A senior Muslim official on
Friday said that the proposal by Yugoslavia on establishing
diplomatic relations with Bosnia is unacceptable.
</P>
<P>
"We are analyizing the document that the Yugoslav foreign
minister's special envoy handed to us and I think it is not
acceptable for Bosnia," said Mirza Hajric, who is an advisor to
Alija Izetbegovic, chairman of the Bosnian presidency.
</P>
<P>
Hajric told the local press that the proposal asks for
withdrawal of Bosnia's suit against Yugoslavia from the
International Court of Justice in The Hague before the
establishment of the bilateral diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
"We are ready for the establishment of diplomatic relations
with Yugoslavia because it is useful for both countries but we
don't want to do it under conditions," Hajric said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the proposal was being studied by legal experts
and the final decision would be taken by the collective presidency
which consists of one representative each from Bosnia's three
ethnic nations.
</P>
<P>
Since the presidential decision is by consensus, it can be
blocked by any side raising objection.
</P>
<P>
Since the signing of Dayton peace accords, Bosnian and Yugoslav
leaders have on several occasions committed themselves to
establishing bilateral relations, but the process has been bogged
down on the issue of Bosnia's charge of aggression against
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Bosnia has claimed that Yugoslavia has instigated the war in
Bosnia, and that if Yugoslavia is not guilty of the aggression, it
should not be afraid of debating in court. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
